SIMPLE: intermix
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermix
<hw>In`ter*mix"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To mix
together; to intermingle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In yonder spring of roses, <qex>intermixed</qex>⟦br⟧
With myrtle, find what to redress till noon.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermix</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intermix
<hw>In`ter*mix"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be mixed together; to be
intermingled.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermixedly</ent>⟦br⟧
